    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but that sounds like a pretty big \"if.\" like, it's one thing to say they might be more efficient later, but if they go bust paying for the equipment and compliance upfront, they won't even be around to see those benefits. do u think the environmental side of this is actually based on solid economic necessity, or is it more just political idealism being forced on industries that cant afford it?",
